To find the configuration file in Manjaro I3, go to the root directory of your system, and digit:

# ls -la

This command will make a list of the directors and files of the current path
You will proceed to search for a ocult directory called .i3

![Screenshot_2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/77154574/158093195-cb980517-7500-428b-9e60-407acf5ac000.png)

Then,you will enter that directory and do the command again:

# ls

You will find a single file called config:

*image with example will be added soon*

Thats the config file of the environment.

*image of the content of the file*
